{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The scoring model assigns the correct risk score when a transaction exceeds the configured amount threshold for its merchant category.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Failure mode: logic/config-application error in deterministic rule scoring (wrong threshold lookup or wrong score math). Required setup: call scoring function/object with transaction + in-memory config containing per-category thresholds and assert numeric score. MOCK-MISS: this behavior is local rule logic, not a cross-module handoff requirement. REAL-INFRA: no OS/network/subprocess needed. LLM-DEP: none; deterministic rules. MULTI-STEP: none. Rejection gate: higher levels are disqualified because behavior text is about 'configured amount threshold' and 'numeric risk score' from rule logic, which is testable in-process.","test_description":"Construct in-memory config with distinct amount thresholds by merchant category; pass a transaction that exceeds its category threshold and assert exact score contribution and total score. Include boundary values (equal to threshold vs just above) to catch off-by-one comparator errors.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.84,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The risk model identifies a fraudulent transaction pattern (e.g., rapid small purchases from different geographies) even when no single rule threshold is exceeded.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure mode: AI/ML judgment-quality error (model fails to recognize fraud pattern from context). Required setup: run real risk model inference on representative pattern cases and verify fraud probability/label behavior. MOCK-HIDE: stubbing model output would trivially pass and hide true detection failures. REAL-INFRA: external call may exist, but core boundary is model quality, so Agentic is the minimum meaningful level. MULTI-STEP: single model decision, not a multi-agent chain. Rejection gate: Workflow is disqualified because behavior specifies one model identification step, not multiple agentic steps in sequence.","test_description":"Use a fixed evaluation set containing known fraud-like sequences (rapid low-amount purchases across geographies, with no individual scoring-rule threshold breach) and assert the real risk model assigns fraud probability above review threshold for those cases at an acceptable hit rate.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.84,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The velocity check in the scoring model correctly counts the number of transactions within the configured time window per user.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure mode: module handoff/wiring error between scoring logic, time-window configuration, clock/timestamp handling, and transaction repository query/filtering. Required setup: wire scorer with repository (or local DB) and seeded transaction history; verify count used by velocity rule. MOCK-MISS: a pure unit test of counting logic can miss boundary bugs in repository filtering/time-window propagation. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no real OS/network/subprocess required; local in-process DB/repo is sufficient, so not System. (b) no AI/ML output dependence, so not Agentic. (c) no multi-agent chain, so not Workflow. Rejection gate: System disqualified because behavior text is only about counting in a configured window per user, which can be exposed with local module wiring.","test_description":"Seed per-user transactions around window boundaries in a local repository (inside, outside, and exactly at boundary); run velocity check through scoring service with configured window and assert counted transaction total is correct and drives expected score increment.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.33,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A transaction flagged by the risk model but not by the scoring model is still held for review — the models operate as an OR gate, not AND.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure mode: orchestration/wiring error in decision combiner (incorrect boolean logic across model outputs). Required setup: integrate model-result adapters with review-decision service and feed mixed outputs (risk=true, score=false). MOCK-MISS: unit-testing a standalone boolean helper may miss mapping/field-name inversions between modules. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no real OS/network/subprocess needed. (b) correctness here does not depend on real AI quality; only consumes already-produced flags/probabilities. (c) no multi-step agentic pipeline. Rejection gate: Agentic disqualified by behavior text focusing on OR-gate hold logic, not whether model prediction itself is correct.","test_description":"Run decision pipeline with stubbed model outputs at module boundaries (risk model indicates fraud, scoring model below threshold) and assert transaction state is 'held_for_review'. Add complementary case (risk=false, score=true) to ensure OR semantics are symmetric.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.66,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The combined output includes both the numeric risk score and the risk model's fraud probability, so the reviewer can see which model flagged the transaction and why.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure mode: data-contract/aggregation error when composing reviewer payload (missing field, wrong mapping, lost explanation metadata). Required setup: wire scoring output + risk output into response assembler and validate emitted schema/content. MOCK-MISS: isolated unit tests on one mapper can miss cross-module field drop/rename issues. INTEGR